But the cost of the new vaccine is likely to be significantly lower, as it converts liver cells into antibody factories.
As Professor Crystal said, a future vaccine for humans could, if he is quite sure, be given to children before they are tempted to try a cigarette, and thus prevent nicotine addiction.
