“Pope Francis has decided to announce his decision to convene the consistory in February in advance so that other meetings that require the participation of cardinals from all over the world can be planned,” Lombardi said.
Jack Valero of Catholic Voices said the number of eligible cardinals is likely to decline by February.
He explained that a pope would usually appoint as many cardinals as necessary, so that the number of eligible cardinals would again be 120, and as many cardinals over 80 as he would like.
